# PHP Debugging
- Use `@dump()` and `dd()` for debugging in Blade templates and PHP files
- Implement proper exception handling and error logging
- Utilize XDebug for step-through debugging when available
- Install and use Query Monitor plugin for database queries
- Use `dump()` for non-terminating inspection and `dd()` to dump and die

```php
// Basic debugging
@dump($variable); // In Blade templates
dump($variable);  // In PHP files

// Dump and die (stops execution after dumping)
dd($variable);    // Works in both Blade and PHP

// Enhanced debugging function
function av_debug($data, $label = null) {
    if ($label) {
        dump([$label => $data]);
    } else {
        dump($data);
    }
}
```

